1. Definition
The Hamming distance between two equal-length strings or vectors is the number of positions with differing symbols. For strings s and t of length n: Hamming(s,t) = sum_{i=0..n-1} [s[i] != t[i]] where [P] = 1 if predicate P true else 0.

2. Binary formula (XOR + popcount)
For binary words a and b of equal length: diff = a XOR b; Hamming(a,b) = popcount(diff). Use hardware popcount or efficient software popcount algorithms.

3. Complexity and space
String-based algorithm: O(n) time, O(1) additional space. Bitwise population-count variants: Wegner loop is O(popcount(diff)) iterations; intrinsics give effectively constant-time per machine word.

4. Minimum distance, error detection & correction
Minimum Hamming distance d_min between codewords defines detection/correction: detect up to d_min-1 errors; correct floor((d_min-1)/2) errors. For k-error-correcting codes require d_min >= 2k+1.

5. Implementation patterns and algorithms
- Signature: hamming_distance(s: string, t: string) -> int. Validate equal length; iterate indices and count mismatches.
- Signature: hamming_distance_bits(x: unsigned, y: unsigned) -> int. Return popcount(x ^ y).
- Software popcount options:
  * Wegner loop: while (v) { v &= v - 1; ++count; }
  * Table lookup for 16-bit chunks: count = table[x & 0xFFFF] + table[x >> 16]
  * Parallel add (SWAR) masks (m1,m2,m4,m8,m16,m32,h01) and shifts for 64-bit words.
  * Use __builtin_popcount / __builtin_popcountll when compiling with GCC/Clang.
- Vectorized and Harley–Seal algorithms for SIMD acceleration on wide registers.

6. Supplementary details (coding theory uses)
- Hamming space: fixed-length words over alphabet size q; properties: metric, satisfies triangle inequality.
- For non-binary alphabets, Hamming distance counts symbol mismatches (no weighting).
- For insertions/deletions prefer Levenshtein; Hamming only for equal-length sequences.

7. Reference API / signatures
- hamming_distance(s: string, t: string) -> int
  Params: s,t strings of equal length. Returns: integer mismatch count. Error if lengths differ.
- hamming_distance_bits(x: unsigned int, y: unsigned int) -> int
  Params: machine-word unsigned ints. Returns: popcount(x ^ y).

